            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to a friend called Paulus (Brussels, 2 March
                    1533)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. He cannot express how much spiritual turmoil has
                            accompanied his time abroad. The worst part is the absence of his
                            friends, but he is consoled by the fact that God will have mercy on
                            Hungary in the end, and they will be able to live happily together
                            again. And if he understands it well, they are trying to make peace, and
                            already the assembly called for 7 February was aimed at this. Paulus,
                            who is closer to things, should write him what they can hope for. 2. He
                            has heard that both Brodarics and Nádasdy are part of the delegation,
                            but he does not know for certain. They used to be his friends, and they
                            always supported peace. Even if they have made mistakes, now they could
                            make them right.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/627F57CB-9529-418F-AC55-D6C921732208
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad Paulum amicum.<note xml:id="note.1">We do not know him more
                        closely.</note></p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Non possum tibi explicare litteris, quantis in hac mea
                    peregrinatione iactatus fuerim animi turbationibus. Quae magnae licet fuerunt
                    usque adeo, ut more humano non parum me plerumque commoverint, tamen quoad a me
                    fieri poterit, has omnes perturbationes forti pertuli animo, et semper meliora
                    rebus adversis exspectavi. Nulla autem, mihi crede, res molestior fuit, quam
                        <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">quod</add> ab amicis, quibus ab ineunte
                    aetate assueveram, abfuerim. Quae res <del corresp="Olahus">uno omnium
                        aliarum</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">una omnem aliam</add> animi
                    mei <del corresp="Olahus">perturbationam</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr"
                        >perturbationem</add><del corresp="Olahus">molestiam</del><add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="corr">molestiamque</add> longe superabat. Neque
                    putabam <del corresp="Olahus">me</del> illis aut infortunio quopiam meo, aut
                    iniquitate rerum praesentium a me longe semotis iucundam <add corresp="Olahus"
                        type="insert">me</add> vitam vivere posse. In omnibus autem hisce molestiis
                    consolabatur me spes Deum optimum maximum nobis omnibus Hungaris ex clementia
                    sua miserturum, et non passurum, ut in perpetuum his iactaremur calamitatibus ac
                    futurum propediem, ut tecum ac cum aliis amicis nostris laetam acturi essemus
                    vitam. Quam nobis occasionem, nisi nunc Deus ipse misericors tribuat, quando
                    intelligam principes agere et moliri, ut pax inter eos <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >ponatur</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">componatur</add>, profecto
                    tardius postea nobis allatam iri arbitrabor. Si <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >etiam</del> enim nunc commissarii partis utriusque, qui ad septimum diem
                    praeteriti mensis Februarii in <placeName>Owar</placeName> volentibus
                    principibus convenerunt, rebus infectis dilabentur, quae postea spes pacis
                    futurae nobis est reliqua? Quare, mi Frater, cuperem a te maximopere scire, qui
                    illuc propius es et omnia melius, quam nos, certiusque intelliges, quid sit ubi
                    constitutum, aut saltem quae spes vobis sit de illorum tractatibus pacem an
                    bellum allaturis. Quarum rerum si me feceris, ut spero, participem non mediocri
                    me afficies beneficio, qui totus ex rebus illis pendeo.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[2.] Audiveram <persName>Stephanum Brodericum</persName><note
                        xml:id="note.2">István Brodarics.</note> et <persName>Thomam
                        Nadasdy</persName>, quibuscum olim quali usi fuerimus amicitia, </p>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/30959003-4F9A-414D-AF25-0DD4EFEB552F
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.4">societate et coniunctione, tute scis, inter alios commissarios
                    partis alterius esse designatos.<note xml:id="note.3">Oláh got this information
                        from Schepper, see Ep. 324. Cap. 2.<ref>olahus.tei.15330218_1</ref></note>
                    Tamen verumne id sit, an non, ignoro.<note xml:id="note.4">Because of this, we
                        can be sure that Oláh had not received Schepper’s letter, see Ep.
                            331.<ref>olahus.tei.15330228_1</ref></note> Si verum est, non parvam in
                    spem ducor, ut eorum opera res ipsa aliquem optatum consequatur finem. Cognovi
                    enim eos fuisse pacis mutuaeque tranquillitatis semper studiosissimos, cuius
                    etiam nunc eos amatores esse cogito. Quod si fecerint omnem anteactae vitae
                    errorem, in quem delapsi fuerant, profecto hac re emendabunt. Vale.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.5"><placeName>Bruxellae</placeName> secunda Martii 1533.</p>
            </div>
